<title>UK: Hall Engineering H1 profits leap.</title>
<headline>Hall Engineering H1 profits leap.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1996-09-12</dateline>
<text>
<p>Six months to June 30 -</p>
<p> Operating profit	 6.08		   vs 2.34</p>
<p> Exceptional credit     1.33		   vs nil</p>
<p> Exceptional charge     2.92		   vs nil</p>
<p> Interest		   2.31		   vs 1.36</p>
<p> Tax			  1.72		   vs 1.02</p>
<p> Net taxed		  3.58		   vs 2.38</p>
<p> Pay date		   Oct 18</p>
<p>Div registration date  Oct 1</p>
<p>NOTE -- Hall Engineering in 1996 first half disposed of its Metal Stockholding Divison for a total of 20.86 million stg. The exceptional items include a profit of 1.33 million stg on the disposal and a writeoff of goodwill of 2.92 million stg.  </p>
<p>			   (million stg unless stated)</p>
<p> Shr (pence)		8.20		   vs 7.41</p>
<p> Dividend (pence)	 3.775		  vs 3.775</p>
<p> Pretax		     5.31		   vs 3.40</p>
<p> Turnover		   129.18		 vs 79.79</p>
